---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../config/site';
---

<Layout
	title="Privacy Policy"
	description="How Petera handles data in the app and on this website."
>
	<section class="article">
		<div class="shell">
			<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
			<p class="muted">Effective date: <span class="code-like">{siteConfig.effectiveDate}</span></p>
			<p class="copy">
				Petera is provided by <span class="code-like">{siteConfig.ownerEntity}</span> ("we", "us",
				or "our"). This Privacy Policy explains how Petera currently handles information when
				you use the app and this website.
			</p>

			<div class="intro-note copy">
				<p>
					In short: Petera is built around on-device reminder data, local notifications, and
					user-initiated export and import. This page explains what that means in practice.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="review-note copy" role="note">
				This is a practical starter privacy policy and should be reviewed before publishing.
			</div>

			<h2>1. Summary</h2>
			<p>
				Petera is designed to be local-first. In the current version: reminder data is stored on
				your device, the app uses on-device notifications to surface reminders, data stays on
				your device unless you explicitly export it, and the app currently focuses on local
				export and local import rather than cloud sync.
			</p>
			<p>
				This website is intended to provide basic product, privacy, and support information.
			</p>

			<h2>2. Information stored in the app</h2>
			<p>Depending on how you use Petera, the app may store information such as:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Reminder titles and reminder settings</li>
				<li>Reminder timing details, such as one-time or repeating setup</li>
				<li>Selected weekdays, time-of-day filters, urgency, spread, and quiet hours</li>
				<li>App preferences such as theme and language</li>
				<li>Optional History records if you choose to enable History</li>
				<li>Optional Insights activity data if you choose to enable Insights</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>3. Local-first storage</h2>
			<p>Petera is currently built around local storage on your device.</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Reminder data is stored locally on device</li>
				<li>Reminders are surfaced using local notifications</li>
				<li>Local export and local import are available under the app's data settings</li>
				<li>Sync features are not part of the current shipped scope</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>4. Export and import</h2>
			<p>Petera includes user-initiated export and import features. In the current version:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Export is manual</li>
				<li>Import is manual</li>
				<li>Encrypted export is the default path</li>
				<li>Import is currently a replace-local-data flow rather than a merge flow</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				If you choose to export your data, the file is created because of your action. You are
				responsible for how you store, share, or back up exported files after export.
			</p>

			<h2>5. Optional History and Insights</h2>
			<p>Some data features in Petera are optional.</p>
			<p><strong>History</strong></p>
			<ul>
				<li>History is off by default</li>
				<li>If enabled, it stores user-meaningful reminder events such as done, paused, or deleted permanently</li>
			</ul>
			<p><strong>Insights</strong></p>
			<ul>
				<li>Insights are off by default</li>
				<li>If enabled, the app can store local reminder activity data to generate descriptive insights</li>
				<li>Behavior-based suggestions are also optional and off by default</li>
			</ul>
			<p>In the current version, insights analysis data is local-only and is excluded from export.</p>

			<h2>6. Notifications</h2>
			<p>
				Petera uses notifications so reminders can appear on your device at meaningful times.
				These notifications are part of the core reminder experience. If notification permission
				is disabled, the app may be less able to surface reminders when you are not already using it.
			</p>

			<h2>7. Data sharing and sale</h2>
			<p>
				In the current product direction, Petera is not built around selling personal data. We
				do not describe the app as an advertising or data-broker service.
			</p>

			<h2>8. Accounts and sync</h2>
			<p>
				The current version of Petera is designed around local reminder management, not
				account-based cloud sync. If account, sync, or online backup features are introduced in
				the future, this Privacy Policy should be updated before those changes are released broadly.
			</p>

			<h2>9. Website data</h2>
			<p>This website is intended to be a simple static informational site.</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Advertising trackers are not intended for this site</li>
				<li>Analytics scripts are not intended for this site</li>
				<li>Marketing cookies are not intended for this site</li>
				<li>Account login systems are not intended for this site</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				However, the site may be hosted by third-party infrastructure such as GitHub Pages and
				related delivery services, which may process standard technical request data as part of
				normal web hosting operations. The exact hosting setup should be reviewed before
				publication so this section remains accurate.
			</p>

			<h2>10. Children's privacy</h2>
			<p>
				Petera is not specifically directed to children under the age of 13. If you believe
				personal information from a child has been provided in a way that creates a legal issue,
				contact us at <span class="code-like">{siteConfig.supportEmail}</span>.
			</p>

			<h2>11. Changes to this policy</h2>
			<p>
				We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we may update the
				effective date shown above.
			</p>

			<h2>12. Contact</h2>
			<p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><span class="code-like">{siteConfig.ownerEntity}</span></li>
				<li><span class="code-like">{siteConfig.supportEmail}</span></li>
				<li><span class="code-like">{siteConfig.countryOrJurisdiction}</span> if applicable</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
